COMPONENT NAME: IKM Sybase IQ Incremental Update
AUTHOR: Oracle
Description: - Integration Knowledge Module - Integrates data into a Sybase AS IQ Server (12.4.3 or later) target table in incremental update mode. - Non-existent rows are inserted; rows that already exist are updated. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled.
Restrictions: - You should use at least Sybase AS IQ 12.4.3 - When an Integration Interface using this Knowledge Module is used from a Package, then the option COMMIT should be set to YES for each Integration Interface composing the Package. - When working with journalized data, if the "Synchronize deletions from journal" is executed, the deleted rows on the target are committed - Comparison of data is made using the Update Key defined in the interface. - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore. - Deletes are commited regardless of the COMMIT option. - COMMIT option is not available, as Sybase AS IQ uses a special versioning concept implying restrictions regarding transaction processing and isolation. Data is always commited at the end of an interface, if successfully completed.
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface.
Identifies and updates rows of the Target Datastore depending on the value of the UPDATE_KEY columns of the target datastore records.
Check this option to synchronize journalized deletions. This option will take effect only if one source table is journalized in your interface.
Check this option if you wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected by flow control in a previous execution of this interface.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
